com.avaya.csta.registration

Interface EndpointRegistrationStateListener

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.EventListener
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    EndpointRegistrationStateAdapter

    public interface EndpointRegistrationStateListener
extends java.util.EventListener
    Allows a DMCC client to receive endpoint registration state events for any DeviceID. If you want your application to be notified of these events, provide a class that implements this interface and provide an implementation for each of the following methods. For those methods you do not wish to be notified of, just implement an empty body. Add your listener implementation using the MonitoringServices.addEndpointRegistrationStateListener() method.

    To stop being notified of the events, remove your listener implementation using the MonitoringServices.removeEndpointRegistrationStateListener() method.

    If multiple listeners are added, then each listener will be notified of events; the corresponding callback will be called on each listener that has been added.

    To learn more about using listeners, see Using Listeners.

    Version:
    $Revision: 1.0 $
    Author:
    AVAYA, Inc.

    • Method Detail

      • registrationEventNotify

        void registrationEventNotify(EndpointRegisteredEvent event)
        Callback method that is called when the endpoint is registered. This event occurs when the endpoint registers (for whatever reason). See the EndpointRegisteredEvent for more information.

        The device parameter that specifies the device that is registered is of type SubjectDeviceID so extracting the device ID is a two-step process: 

         SubjectDeviceID subjDeviceID = event.getDevice();
 DeviceID deviceID = subjDeviceID.getDeviceIdentifier();

        Parameters:
        EndpointRegisteredEvent - indication that the endpoint is now registered. Use event.getEndpointAddress() to determine the source IP of the registration.

      • registrationEventNotify

        void registrationEventNotify(EndpointUnregisteredEvent event)
        Callback method that is called when the endpoint is unregistered from the switching function. This event occurs when the endpoint unregisters (for whatever reason). A reason for the unregistration will be present in the event. See the EndpointUnregisteredEvent for more information.

        The device parameter that specifies the device that is unregistered is of type SubjectDeviceID so extracting the device ID is a two-step process: 

         SubjectDeviceID subjDeviceID = event.getDevice();
 DeviceID deviceID = subjDeviceID.getDeviceIdentifier();

        Parameters:
        EndpointUnregisteredEvent - indication that the endpoint is now unregistered. Use event.getReason() or event.getCode()to determine the cause of the unregistration.

      • registrationEventNotify

        void registrationEventNotify(MonitorStop event)
        Callback method that is called when the endpoint is no longer being monitored by the switching function. This event occurs when the Communication Manager switch fails or is restarted.

        Parameters:
        MonitorStop - indication that the endpoint is no longer being monitored.

      • terminated

        void terminated()
        A callback function which is automatically invoked on a listener previously added to a deviceID.
